***************/
@60000 = ~Wands are 1 1/4 ft. long and slender. They are made of ivory, bone, or wood and are usually tipped with something—metal, crystal, stone, and so on. They are fragile and tend to break easily. Because of this, they are often kept in cases.

Wands are powered by charges, each use costing one or more charges (depending on the item). When a wand runs out of charges, it is consumed and destroyed.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 1~


/****************
*   1st Level   *
****************/
//Grease
@60001 = ~Wand of Grease~
@60002 = ~When activated, the wand will create a slippery layer of a fatty, greasy nature to cover a material surface. Any creature entering the area or caught in it when the spell is cast must save or slip and slide, unable to move effectively. Those who successfully save can move, albeit slowly, for the rest of the round (but will need to save vs. Wand again the following round). Those who remain in the area are allowed a Saving Throw each round until they escape the area.

STATISTICS:
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Charge abilities:
– Grease
  – Covers a surface with a slippery layer
  – Any creature within the area must save or slip and slide, each round
  – Saving creatures can move slowly for the rest of the round
  Range: 30 ft.
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand at +2

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~

//Armor
@60003 = ~Wand of Armor~
@60004 = ~When activated, the wand generates a magical field of force that serves as if it were scale mail armor. This does not hinder movement, adds no weight or encumbrance, and doesn't prevent spellcasting.

STATISTICS:
(Conjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Armor
  – Applies a field of magical force of armor around the wielder (AC 6).
  – Does not affect spellcasting or thieving skills
  Duration: 9 hours
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Burning Hands
@60005 = ~Wand of Burning Hands~
@60006 = ~When activated, a jet of searing flame shoots forward in a horizontal arc of about 120 degrees, with a 5 ft. length. Any creature in the area of the flames suffers 1d3 +%magnitude%  points of fire damage. Those successfully saving vs. Wand receive half damage.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Burning Hands
  – Creates a fan-line cone of fire 5 ft. from the wielder
  Damage: 1d3 +%magnitude% points of fire damage
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: 5-ft. cone with 120-deg. arc
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand for 1/2 damage

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Charm Person
@60007 = ~Wand of Charm Person~
@60008 = ~This wand will charm its humanoid† target when activated; the charmed individual may be given orders, and they will carry them out as quickly as possible. They will also gladly provide valuable information to their new ally.

If the caster harms, or attempts to harm, the charmed person by some overt action, or if Dispel Magic is successfully cast upon the charmed person, the charm spell is broken. If two or more charm effects simultaneously affect a creature, the most recent charm takes precedence. Note that the subject has full memory of the events that took place while <PRO_HESHE> was charmed. Also note that you cannot have a charmed creature leave the area where <PRO_HESHE> was charmed.

†: Humanoids are any bipedal human, demihuman, or humanoid of man-size or smaller, such as brownies, dryads, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, troglodytes, and others. Thus, a 10th-level fighter could be charmed, but an ogre could not.

STATISTICS:
(Enchantment/Charm)

Charge abilities:
– Charm Person
  – Charms the target to be ordered or spoken to
  Range: Visual range
  Duration: 5 rounds
  Area of Effect: 1 person
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand (at +3) negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Color Spray
@60009 = ~Wand of Color Spray~
@60010 = ~This wand will project a vivid, fan-shaped spray of clashing colors to spring forth from itself, causing 1d6 creatures within the area to be affected in order of increasing distance. All creatures affected that have 4 Hit Dice or less must make a successful Saving Throw or be rendered unconscious for 5 rounds.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Color Spray
  – Renders 1d6 creatures unconsious (in order of increasing distance)
  – Only creatures with < 5 HD affected
  Range: 50 ft.
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: 90-degree arc
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand negates (if HD > %caster_level% or > HD 6)

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Blindness
@60011 = ~Wand of Blindness~
@60012 = ~This wand will flash, temporarily blinding its target. If a victim is blinded, <PRO_HESHE> receives a -4 penalty to <PRO_HISHER> attack rolls and Armor Class.

STATISTICS:
(Illusion/Phantasm)

Charge abilities:
– Blindness
  – Temporarily blinds its target
    – -4 penalty to AC
    – -4 penalty to attack rolls
  Range: 40 ft.
  Duration: 2 hours
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Friends
@60013 = ~Wand of Friends~
@60014 = ~This wand will temporarily grant 6 points of Charisma to the wielder. Those who view the affected tend to be very impressed with <PRO_HIMHER> and make an effort to be <PRO_HISHER> friends and help <PRO_HIMHER>, as appropriate to the situation. Officious bureaucrats might decide to become helpful; surly gate guards might wax informative; attacking orcs might spare the caster's life, taking <PRO_HIMHER> captive instead.

STATISTICS:
(Enchantment/Charm)

Charge abilities:
– Friends
  – Temporarily gain 6 points of Charisma
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Protection from Petrification
@60015 = ~Wand of Protection from Petrification~
@60016 = ~This wand will grant the recipient immunity to all petrification attacks; this includes basilisk and medusa gaze, cursed scrolls of petrification, etc.

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Protection from Petrification
  – Immunity to all petrification attacks
  Range: Touch
  Duration: 1 hour
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Identify
@60017 = ~Wand of Identify~
@60018 = ~This wand will use 1 charge to identify an item, much like a scroll of Identify, in that to identify an item you right-click on that item. A menu will appear and from here you choose the "Scroll" option. The chance of identifying the item is 100%. The charge will identify the item's name, what it does, and if it is cursed.

STATISTICS:
(Divination)

Charge abilities:
– Identify
  – Identify an item by using 1 charge
  Range: Touch
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: 1 item
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Infravision
@60019 = ~Wand of Infravision~
@60020 = ~This wand will grant the ability to see with infravision, just as an elf or dwarf can.

STATISTICS:
(Divination)

Charge abilities:
– Infravision
  – Ability to see with infravision
  Range: 30 ft.
  Duration: 2 hours
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Magic Missile
@60021 = ~Wand of Magic Missiles~
@60022 = ~When activated, the wand will eject a missiles of magical energy that dart forth and unerringly strikes its target. This includes enemy creatures in a melee. The target creature must be seen or otherwise detected to be hit, however, so near-total concealment, such as that offered by arrow slits, can render the spell ineffective. Each missile will inflict 1d4+1 points of damage.

STATISTICS:
(Evocation)

Charge abilities:
– Magic Missile
  – %magnitude% magic missiles will strike the target
  Damage: 1d4+1 per missile
  Range: Sight
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Protection from Evil
@60023 = ~Wand of Protection from Evil~
@60024 = ~When activated, the wand creates a magical barrier around the recipient at a distance of one foot. The barrier moves with the recipient and has two major effects: First, the protected creature gets a +2 bonus to AC and saving throws against attacks made by evil or evilly enchanted creatures. Second, summoned demons cannot target the protected creature.

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Protection from Evil
  – +2 AC bonus against attacks from Evil creatures
  – +2 Saving Throw bonus against attacks from Evil creatures
  – Protected from summoned demons
  Range: Touch
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 1 creature

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Shield
@60025 = ~Wand of Shield~
@60026 = ~When activated, the wand generates an invisible barrier in front of the wielder, granting a +4 AC bonus for the shield against melee and +2 against ranged, also granting immunity from the spell Magic Missile.

STATISTICS:
(Evocation)

Charge abilities:
– Shield
